neighborhood_overview:
Our place is located in the center area of Tokyo city , within walking distance to the Imperial Palace, Tokyo Station, Ginza and Akihabara (within 15-20min);near to the Bank of Japan, the Mitsukoshi Isetan department store, the Muromachi shopping center, etc., where you can buy Japanese souvenirs and enjoy Japanese food.
There are many subway routes in the area, including the JR line, the Ginza line, the Hanzomon line, the Hibiya line, the Asakusa line, and so on.
It is a 4-minutes walk from Mitsukoshimae Station ( Metro Ginza Line and Metro Hanzomon Line) , and a 4-minute walk from Kodenmacho Station ( Metro Hibiya Line).
It is also very convenient for visitors, who come and go to Narita and Haneda airports. There is a shuttle bus from the airport to Tokyo Station and this way ,currently, is the most comfortable, cheapest and fastest route. We are located just 15 minutes walk from Tokyo Station .

name: Licensed Tokyo Rental - Cozy Sakurashinmachi
description: Located less than 10 minutes away from Shibuya and its famous crossing, Sakurashinmachi is conveniently located near but very much out of the Hustle of the mega-city. A quiet, cozy, and family friendly area, there are many convenient, unique, and nearby supermarkets, shops, restaurants, and parks to explore. It is located just a short walk from the station. The building is split with vacation rentals and real Japanese tenants, so you will experience the Japanese lifestyle like a locale.
neighborhood_overview: Sakurashinmachi is a nice, quiet suburban neighborhood out of the dense Tokyo city center, but close enough to reach the city in less than 20 minutes. As such, there are many convenient shops, supermarkets, and family friendly places. This apartment building is shared by real Japanese long term tenants, so you will receive a much more authentic Japanese experience compared to a hotel or more within the city.

The area is bounded by the Sumida River to the east, Kiyosubashi Street to the west, Kuramaebashi Street to the south, and Asakusa Street to the north.

Stylish shops and cafes run by designers and creators are opening one after another in the neighborhood, attracting a lot of attention from the younger generation.

neighborhood_overview:
The Great Kanto Earthquake occurred in September 1923. Around the same period this house was built. As a store, factory, or dormitory, from one corner of the back alley of Tsukiji Market, the house witnessed the city's reconstruction, and the drastic changes that stroke Japan spanning from food to politics.
And now, I would like to invite you to think about and imagine the new stories for the next 100-years journey in front of us.

Tokyo 28 minutes from the station.

description:
Perfect Location!
Early luggage drop-off and post-checkout luggage storage are both okay! Early check-in is fine if the room is ready.

Enjoy your stay just 2 minutes from Higashi Shinjuku Station, within walking distance to Shinjuku, Kabukicho, and Shin-Okubo. Easy access via limousine bus from Kabukicho Tower. The hotel is next to Kabukicho, Japan's largest entertainment district, with Don Quijote, convenience stores, and supermarkets nearby for easy shopping.
neighborhood_overview:
The hotel is conveniently located in Okubo, Shinjuku-ku, Tokyo.
The nearest station is a 2-minute walk from Higashi Shinjuku Station on the Tokyo Metro Fukutoshin Line, an 8-minute walk from Shin-Okubo Station on the JR Yamanote Line, and a 10-minute walk from Seibu Shinjuku Station on the Seibu Shinjuku Line, providing very convenient access to central Tokyo.
The surrounding area offers a wide variety of multinational restaurants, with the Shin-Okubo area in particular offering Korean cuisine, and the close proximity to Shinjuku's downtown area and Kabukicho allows residents to enjoy nighttime entertainment.
Furthermore, the Shinjuku Gyoen Garden and the Tokyo Metropolitan Government Building Observation Deck are nearby as tourist attractions, allowing residents to experience the beauty of nature and the charm of the city all at once.
Shopping is also plentiful, with large department stores and specialty stores where you can pick up fashion and souvenirs.
